Let 
\begin_inset Formula $(x,u(x))$
\end_inset

 be the curve from 
\begin_inset Formula $(0,0)$
\end_inset

 to 
\begin_inset Formula $(1,-1)$
\end_inset

 where the first coordinate is the 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 axis and the second coordinate is the 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 axis.
 Suppose that this is the curve that takes the shortest time for a bead
 to slide along the curve frictionlessly from 
\begin_inset Formula $(0,0)$
\end_inset

 to 
\begin_inset Formula $(1,-1)$
\end_inset

 under uniform gravity.
 Then, we have that
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
2uu''+(u')^{2}+1=0.
\]

